`crates/ctx-verify` is a standalone binary crate: a broker that spawns cargo/clippy/script checks and emits one capped, deterministic report (terse text or JSON) via `cli::run`. Depending on this crate means depending on `ctx_verify::cli::run` and the `model::Report`/`CheckReport` JSON contract.

The crate has two peer subtrees: `src/` implements the strict layering `main.rs → cli.rs → checks.rs → runner.rs`, with `parse.rs` and `model.rs` defining the diagnostic/report shapes and `error.rs` the shared `CheckError` enum. `tests/` is a fully faked black-box suite (`FakeRunner`, no real subprocesses) that pins both the parser/orchestration layer and the CLI rendering layer against that contract.

The critical cross-cutting coupling: any change to how `checks.rs` invokes a tool — new flag, reordered args, a new script path — must be mirrored in three places at once: the parser choice in `checks.rs`, and the independently-built `by_first_arg` fake-command maps in both test files. Diagnostic capping/truncation and `CheckError` variants are likewise pinned by both source and test layers, so a schema change to `model::Diagnostic` or a new `CheckError` variant touches `checks.rs`, `parse.rs`, `cli.rs` match sites, and both test files' assertions together.

No intent.md exists for this directory, so no divergence can be assessed.